27/10/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic arrives on a two-day visit to Tirana on Monday (27 October) at the invitation of his Albanian counterpart, Alfred Moisiu. 
During the visit, two bilateral agreements will be signed -- one on co-operation in the healthcare sector, the other in the customs sector. 
The visit will be Mesic's second to Albania in less than three years.
In other news, Croatia's Defence Ministry says the pace of reforms is satisfactory, as is the process of staff downsizing. 
The assessment came from the head of the ministry's personnel department, Brigadier Zeljko Valentic, who participated in a seminar on defence sector reforms Sunday. 
(HINA, BBC - 26/10/03)
